<subSubSection id="A82ECBA1382B7E1127ADA6712F15B3CE" pageId="4" pageNumber="99" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="2EFDFC047F3A36300FD1F4FA17BCDFED" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="184D63AA765D88DD2691DEA684DB2A84" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">
The specific epithet ' 
<taxonomicName id="71CF239EC27681E70E0597B262FFE93A" authorityName="Y. S. Chao &amp; W. L. Chiou" authorityYear="2017" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Pteris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="latipinna" order="Polypodiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="99" phylum="Pteridophyta" rank="species" species="latipinna">latipinna</taxonomicName>
' refers to its wide pinnae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="55E10014ACB3C31B971382918ACD323F" pageId="4" pageNumber="99" type="preliminary conservation assessment">
<paragraph id="E92DEC83D48BD13CCCD97DF86F0875A0" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">Preliminary conservation assessment.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="118210467974AA55C6371593D831EF46" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">
We investigated the distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="98F0D3916027A76082A61AFB1C5EE838" class="Filicopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. latipinna" order="Polypodiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="99" phylum="Pteridophyta" rank="species" species="latipinna">
<emphasis id="D72D1620C017AB083644DB57EAA55E5C" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">P. latipinna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Y.S.Chao &amp; W.L.Chiou, sp. nov. in Taiwan. To date, only a few small populations are recorded. However, the available information is inadequate to support the assessment of its extinction risk. According to the 
<bibRefCitation id="B65D5C585191106EF5620F51326A8F90" author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK" pageId="8" pageNumber="103" publicationUrl="http://cmsdocs.s3.amazonaws.com/keydocuments/Categories_and_Criteria_en_web%2Bcover%2Bbckcover.pdf" refId="B13" refString="IUCN, 2012. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria (Version 2). Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, http://cmsdocs.s3.amazonaws.com/keydocuments/Categories_and_Criteria_en_web%2Bcover%2Bbckcover.pdf" title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria (Version 2)." url="http://cmsdocs.s3.amazonaws.com/keydocuments/Categories_and_Criteria_en_web%2Bcover%2Bbckcover.pdf" year="2012">IUCN (2012)</bibRefCitation>
criteria, the category of Data Deficient (DD) is appropriate.
</paragraph>
